article.headline: Manhattan 78, Iona 74
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jeff Xavier scored 23 points and Manhattan rallied in the second half to defeat Iona 78-74 Sunday night and win the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference title in the final regular-season game for both teams. Jason Wingate scored 16 points, Devon Austin had 12, and Arturo Dubois had 11 points and 14 rebounds for the Jaspers (18-9, 14-4), who earned a bye into the semifinals of next weekend's MAAC tournament. Steve Burtt scored 24 points and Ricky Soliver had 11 points and 12 rebounds for the Gaels (20-7, 13-5), who would have won the MAAC with a victory. In finishing in second , Iona earned a bye into the MAAC quarterfinals. The Gaels, who led by seven at the break, were ahead by as much as 44-34 after Soliver scored 1:23 into the second half. Wingate nailed two free throws to cap an 18-7 run that gave Manhattan its first lead in the second half at 52-51 with 11:02 remaining. Soliver scored with 3:16 left to give Iona a 70-67 lead. Dubois then scored to cut the edge to 70-69, Mike Konovelchick tied it on a free throw with 2:31 left and Wingate's basket with 1:58 to go provided the Jaspers with a 72-70 lead. There were 55 fouls whistled in the game that produced 11 lead changes and five ties, with Manhattan converting 26-of-32 free throws and Iona going 24-for-35.
